[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Demonstration of JS-Eden"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## How to use \"is\":"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Define 2 variables with one observing the other through is."]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["a = 5;","b is a * 2;"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Change a and watch b update to use the new value of a"]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["a = 10;"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## How to use \"when\":"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Define a when block. This will be triggered whenever the condition is true."]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["c = true;","d = 1;","when(c == true){","    d = d + 1;","}"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Change c between true and false and watch the when condition be triggered multiple times and increment d."]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["c = true;"]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["c = false;"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Use the picture variable to define what the canvas should display"]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["picture1 is [","    Text(\"Draw Shapes\", 25, 50, 24, \"white\"),","    Rectangle(100, 100, 50, 50, \"red\"),","    Circle(350, 200, 60, \"green\"),","    Line(100, 400, 400, 400, \"blue\")","];"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## The picture can reference other variables"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Change x and y to update the picture. You can use the variable sliders."]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["x = 0;","y = 0;","","picture1 is [","    Text(\"Move Shapes by changing variables\", 25, 50, 24, \"white\"),","    Rectangle(50 + x * 5, 100 + y * 5, 50, 50, \"red\")","];"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Use mouseX and mouseY to get the mouse coordinates"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["This picture uses mouseX and mouseY to create a circle that follows the mouse around the canavs display."]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["x is mouseX;","y is mouseY;","","picture1 is [","    Text(\"Follow the mouse\", 25, 50, 24, \"white\"),","    Circle(x, y, 60, \"green\")","];"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Use mousePressed to get when the mouse has been pressed"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["This example uses mousePressed in a when condition to move the circle to the mouse coodinates whenever the mouse is pressed."]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["x = 100;","y = 200;","","when(mousePressed == true){","    x = mouseX;","    y = mouseY;","}","","picture1 is [","    Text(\"Click to trigger events\", 25, 50, 24, \"white\"),","    Circle(x, y, 60, \"green\")","];"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Use this knowledge to create more complex ideas"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["This example displays the solar system. Change the tick variable to make the planets move round their orbit."]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["tick = 0;","","originX = 350;","originY = 350;","","sun is Circle(originX, originY, 30, \"gold\", \"none\");","","earthDistance = 150;","earthX is originX + sin(tick) * earthDistance;","earthY is originY + cos(tick) * earthDistance;","earth is Circle(earthX, earthY, 10, \"green\", \"none\");","","mercury_distance = 0.39;","venus_distance = 0.72;","mars_distance = 1.52;","","mercury_speed = 0.24;","venus_speed = 0.62;","mars_speed = 1.9;","","mercury_size = 5;","venus_size = 8;","mars_size = 6.5;","","mercuryX is originX + sin(tick / mercury_speed) * earthDistance * mercury_distance;","mercuryY is originY + cos(tick / mercury_speed) * earthDistance * mercury_distance;","mercury_colour is \"blue\";","","mercury is Circle(mercuryX, mercuryY, mercury_size, mercury_colour, \"none\");","","venus is mercury with","\tmercury_distance is venus_distance,","\tmercury_speed is venus_speed,","\tmercury_colour is \"pink\",","    mercury_size is venus_size;","","mars is mercury with","\tmercury_distance is mars_distance,","\tmercury_speed is mars_speed,","\tmercury_colour is \"red\",","    mercury_size is mars_size;","","","picture1 is [","    Text(\"Create models, eg. the solar system\", 25, 50, 24, \"white\"),","    sun, earth, mercury, venus, mars","];"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["The Counter function can be set to increment a variable periodically. Here the tick variable is set in the counter which creates an animation of the planets orbiting a star."]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["c = Counter(&tick, 30);","","picture1 is [","    Text(\"Animate models, eg. the solar system\", 25, 50, 24, \"white\"),","    sun, earth, mercury, venus, mars","];"]}]